  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "לכם הבוּ, give here, provide for yourselves. The congregation was to nominate, according to its tribes, wise, intelligent, and well-known men, whom Moses would appoint as heads, i.e., as judges, over the nation. At their installation he gave them the requisite instructions (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 1:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): \"Ye shall hear between your brethren,\" i.e., hear both parties as mediators, \"and judge righteously, without respect of person.\" פּנים הכּיר, to look at the face, equivalent to פּנים נשׁא (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 19:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), i.e., to act partially (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 23:2-3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). \"The judgment is God's,\" i.e., appointed by God, and to be administered in the name of God, or in accordance with His justice; hence the expression \"to bring before God\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 21:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 22:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
